<subSubSection lastPageId="11" lastPageNumber="462" pageId="9" pageNumber="460" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="9.[151,1437,1455,2023]" lastBlockId="11.[151,1437,151,393]" lastPageId="11" lastPageNumber="462" pageId="9" pageNumber="460">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,315,1852,1878]" pageId="9" pageNumber="460">Remarks.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName authority="Prell, 1913" authorityName="Prell" authorityYear="1913" box="[322,681,1852,1878]" class="Insecta" family="Dynastidae" genus="Eophileurus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="9" pageNumber="460" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="felschei">
<emphasis box="[322,552,1852,1878]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="460">Eophileurus felschei</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Prell, H." box="[558,681,1852,1878]" pageId="9" pageNumber="460" pagination="103 - 124" refId="ref17521" refString="Prell, H. (1913) Beitrage zur Kenntnis der Dynastinen. viii. Ueber das Genus Eophilurus Arrow. Memoires de la Societe Entomologique de Belgique, 22, 103 - 124." type="journal article" year="1913">Prell, 1913</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
was described based on one pair of specimens from “Genji, 
<collectingCountry box="[1359,1422,1852,1878]" name="India" pageId="9" pageNumber="460">India</collectingCountry>
”. The 
<typeStatus box="[204,307,1888,1914]" pageId="9" pageNumber="460">lectotype</typeStatus>
(
<figureCitation box="[323,460,1888,1914]" captionStart="FIGURES 38–48" captionStartId="10.[151,264,1944,1968]" captionTargetBox="[253,1339,186,1912]" captionTargetId="figure-18@10.[241,1346,181,1920]" captionTargetPageId="10" captionText="FIGURES 38–48. Type specimens of Eophileurus felschei Prell, 1913. 38–31, lectotype, female, 38, habitus, dorsal; 39, habitus, lateral; 40, habitus, ventral; 41, labels; 42–48, lectoparatype, male (images ©MTD/Olaf Jäger), 42, habitus, dorsal; 43, habitus, lateral; 44, habitus, ventral, 45–46, parameres, apical; 47, parameres, lateral; 48, labels." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6853956" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6853956/files/figure.png" pageId="9" pageNumber="460">Figs. 38–41</figureCitation>
) was designated by 
<bibRefCitation author="Endrodi, S." box="[694,870,1888,1914]" pageId="9" pageNumber="460" pagination="93 - 134" refId="ref16934" refString="Endrodi, S. (1977) Monographie de Dynastinae VIII Tribus Phileurini. Entomologische Abhandlungen Staatlichen Museum fur Tierkunde Dresden, 41 (4), 93 - 134. https: // doi. org / 10.1515 / 9783112546161" type="journal article" year="1977">Endrődi (1977)</bibRefCitation>
, which is the female specimen housed in MFNB. The 
<typeStatus box="[201,352,1924,1950]" pageId="9" pageNumber="460">paralectotype</typeStatus>
(
<figureCitation box="[366,499,1924,1950]" captionStart="FIGURES 38–48" captionStartId="10.[151,264,1944,1968]" captionTargetBox="[253,1339,186,1912]" captionTargetId="figure-18@10.[241,1346,181,1920]" captionTargetPageId="10" captionText="FIGURES 38–48. Type specimens of Eophileurus felschei Prell, 1913. 38–31, lectotype, female, 38, habitus, dorsal; 39, habitus, lateral; 40, habitus, ventral; 41, labels; 42–48, lectoparatype, male (images ©MTD/Olaf Jäger), 42, habitus, dorsal; 43, habitus, lateral; 44, habitus, ventral, 45–46, parameres, apical; 47, parameres, lateral; 48, labels." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6853956" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6853956/files/figure.png" pageId="9" pageNumber="460">Figs. 42–48</figureCitation>
) of this species is the male specimen housed in MTD. In recent years, 
<bibRefCitation author="Dupuis, F." box="[1275,1436,1924,1950]" pageId="9" pageNumber="460" pagination="13 - 18" refId="ref16872" refString="Dupuis, F. (2014) Deux nouvelles especes d' Eophileurus Arrow, 1908. Coleopteres, 20 (3), 13 - 18." type="journal article" year="2014">Dupuis (2014)</bibRefCitation>
described 
<taxonomicName authority="Dupuis, 2014" authorityName="Dupuis" authorityYear="2014" box="[266,637,1960,1986]" class="Insecta" family="Dynastidae" genus="Eophileurus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="9" pageNumber="460" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="grossepunctatus">
<emphasis box="[266,478,1961,1986]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="460">E. grossepunctatus</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Dupuis, F." box="[485,637,1960,1986]" pageId="9" pageNumber="460" pagination="13 - 18" refId="ref16872" refString="Dupuis, F. (2014) Deux nouvelles especes d' Eophileurus Arrow, 1908. Coleopteres, 20 (3), 13 - 18." type="journal article" year="2014">Dupuis, 2014</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
from “Shimoga, 
<collectingCountry box="[832,892,1960,1986]" name="India" pageId="9" pageNumber="460">India</collectingCountry>
” (
<typeStatus box="[917,1027,1960,1986]" pageId="9" pageNumber="460">Holotype</typeStatus>
: 
<figureCitation box="[1038,1171,1960,1987]" captionStart="FIGURES 49–53" captionStartId="11.[151,264,1333,1357]" captionTargetBox="[156,1433,418,1309]" captionTargetId="figure-149@11.[151,1435,417,1309]" captionTargetPageId="11" captionText="FIGURES 49–53. Holotype of Eophileurus grossepunctatus Dupuis, 2014 (images ©MNHN/A. Mantilleri). 49, habitus, dorsal; 50, habitus, lateral; 51, parameres, apical; 52, parameres, lateral; 53, labels." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6853958" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6853958/files/figure.png" pageId="9" pageNumber="460">Figs. 49–53</figureCitation>
) without providing any comparison to 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Prell" authorityYear="1913" box="[315,431,1996,2022]" class="Insecta" family="Dynastidae" genus="Eophileurus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="9" pageNumber="460" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="felschei">
<emphasis box="[315,431,1996,2022]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="460">E. felschei</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. After the examination of the type material of both taxa, it is clear that no major differences are present in both the appearance and the parameres other than slight differences on the lateral processes of the parameres of the 
<specimenCount box="[343,445,187,213]" pageId="11" pageNumber="462" type="male">two male</specimenCount>
types (the lateral processes are slightly more enlarged and expanded at their apices in the type of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Prell" authorityYear="1913" box="[238,355,223,249]" class="Insecta" family="Dynastidae" genus="Eophileurus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="11" pageNumber="462" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="felschei">
<emphasis box="[238,355,223,249]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="462">E. felschei</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and less so in 
<emphasis box="[521,741,223,248]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="462">
<taxonomicName authorityName="Dupuis" authorityYear="2014" box="[521,737,223,248]" class="Insecta" family="Dynastidae" genus="Eophileurus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="11" pageNumber="462" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="grossepunctatus">E. grossepunctatus</taxonomicName>
.
</emphasis>
This mild difference can be seen in 
<figureCitation box="[1150,1230,223,249]" captionStart="FIGURES 38–48" captionStartId="10.[151,264,1944,1968]" captionTargetBox="[253,1339,186,1912]" captionTargetId="figure-18@10.[241,1346,181,1920]" captionTargetPageId="10" captionText="FIGURES 38–48. Type specimens of Eophileurus felschei Prell, 1913. 38–31, lectotype, female, 38, habitus, dorsal; 39, habitus, lateral; 40, habitus, ventral; 41, labels; 42–48, lectoparatype, male (images ©MTD/Olaf Jäger), 42, habitus, dorsal; 43, habitus, lateral; 44, habitus, ventral, 45–46, parameres, apical; 47, parameres, lateral; 48, labels." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6853956" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6853956/files/figure.png" pageId="11" pageNumber="462">Fig. 46</figureCitation>
versus 
<figureCitation box="[1316,1396,222,249]" captionStart="FIGURES 49–53" captionStartId="11.[151,264,1333,1357]" captionTargetBox="[156,1433,418,1309]" captionTargetId="figure-149@11.[151,1435,417,1309]" captionTargetPageId="11" captionText="FIGURES 49–53. Holotype of Eophileurus grossepunctatus Dupuis, 2014 (images ©MNHN/A. Mantilleri). 49, habitus, dorsal; 50, habitus, lateral; 51, parameres, apical; 52, parameres, lateral; 53, labels." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6853958" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6853958/files/figure.png" pageId="11" pageNumber="462">Fig. 52</figureCitation>
for the front view, and 
<figureCitation box="[366,444,259,285]" captionStart="FIGURES 38–48" captionStartId="10.[151,264,1944,1968]" captionTargetBox="[253,1339,186,1912]" captionTargetId="figure-18@10.[241,1346,181,1920]" captionTargetPageId="10" captionText="FIGURES 38–48. Type specimens of Eophileurus felschei Prell, 1913. 38–31, lectotype, female, 38, habitus, dorsal; 39, habitus, lateral; 40, habitus, ventral; 41, labels; 42–48, lectoparatype, male (images ©MTD/Olaf Jäger), 42, habitus, dorsal; 43, habitus, lateral; 44, habitus, ventral, 45–46, parameres, apical; 47, parameres, lateral; 48, labels." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6853956" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6853956/files/figure.png" pageId="11" pageNumber="462">Fig. 47</figureCitation>
versus 
<figureCitation box="[529,607,258,285]" captionStart="FIGURES 49–53" captionStartId="11.[151,264,1333,1357]" captionTargetBox="[156,1433,418,1309]" captionTargetId="figure-149@11.[151,1435,417,1309]" captionTargetPageId="11" captionText="FIGURES 49–53. Holotype of Eophileurus grossepunctatus Dupuis, 2014 (images ©MNHN/A. Mantilleri). 49, habitus, dorsal; 50, habitus, lateral; 51, parameres, apical; 52, parameres, lateral; 53, labels." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6853958" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6853958/files/figure.png" pageId="11" pageNumber="462">Fig. 51</figureCitation>
for the lateral view). Following the conclusion of the discussion section at the end of this paper, it is observed that the lateral processes bare the largest individual and geographical variations, and with differences this mild, the differences are too insignificant to separate them from a single species. Hence, 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Dupuis" authorityYear="2014" class="Insecta" family="Dynastidae" genus="Eophileurus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="11" pageNumber="462" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="grossepunctatus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="462">E. grossepunctatus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is conspecific with 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Prell" authorityYear="1913" box="[556,673,367,393]" class="Insecta" family="Dynastidae" genus="Eophileurus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="11" pageNumber="462" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="felschei">
<emphasis box="[556,673,367,393]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="462">E. felschei</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and thus synonymized here.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
